Oil traders in the New York area saidExxon Corp's Exxon U.S.A. unit reduced the price it chargescontract barge customers for heating oil in New York harbor0.50 cent a gallon, effective today.    They said the reduction brings Exxon's contract barge priceto 49.75. The price decrease follows sharp declines in heatingoil prices in the spot and futures markets, traders said. Reuter&#3;